member.name: T:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode
member.summary: Provides enumeration over the PEPPOL VAT exemption codes
member.remarks: https://docs.peppol.eu/poacc/billing/3.0/codelist/vatex/

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_79_C
member.summary: Exempt based on article 79, point c of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-79-C)
member.remarks: Exemptions relating to repayment of expenditures. Remark, Repayment of expenditure is not an exemption in the sense of the VAT Directive but may be handled as such in the context of the EN16931.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132 of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132)
member.remarks: Exemptions for certain activities in public interest.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1A
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (a) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1A)
member.remarks: The supply by the public postal services of services other than passenger transport and telecommunications services, and the supply of goods incidental thereto.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1B
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (b) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1B)
member.remarks: Hospital and medical care and closely related activities undertaken by bodies governed by public law or, under social conditions comparable with those applicable to bodies governed by public law, by hospitals, centres for medical treatment or diagnosis and other duly recognised establishments of a similar nature

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1C
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (c) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1C)
member.remarks: The provision of medical care in the exercise of the medical and paramedical professions as defined by the Member State concerned.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1D
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (d) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1D)
member.remarks: The supply of human organs, blood and milk.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1E
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (e) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1E)
member.remarks: The supply of services by dental technicians in their professional capacity and the supply of dental prostheses by dentists and dental technicians.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1F
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (f) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1F)
member.remarks: The supply of services by independent groups of persons, who are carrying on an activity which is exempt from VAT or in relation to which they are not taxable persons, for the purpose of rendering their members the services directly necessary for the exercise of that activity, where those groups merely claim from their members exact reimbursement of their share of the joint expenses, provided that such exemption is not likely to cause distortion of competition.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1G
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (g) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1G)
member.remarks: The supply of services and of goods closely linked to welfare and social security work, including those supplied by old people's homes, by bodies governed by public law or by other bodies recognised by the Member State concerned as being devoted to social wellbeing.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1H
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (h) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1H)
member.remarks: "The supply of services and of goods closely linked to the protection of children and young persons by bodies governed by public law or by other organisations recognised by the Member State concerned as being devoted to social wellbeing"

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1I
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (i) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1I)
member.remarks: " The provision of children's or young people's education, school or university education, vocational training or retraining, including the supply of services and of goods closely related thereto, by bodies governed by public law having such as their aim or by other organisations recognised by the Member State concerned as having similar objects."

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1J
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (j) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1J)
member.remarks: Tuition given privately by teachers and covering school or university education.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1K
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (k) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1K)
member.remarks: The supply of staff by religious or philosophical institutions for the purpose of the activities referred to in points (b), (g), (h) and (i) and with a view to spiritual welfare.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1L
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (l) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1L)
member.remarks: The supply of services, and the supply of goods closely linked thereto, to their members in their common interest in return for a subscription fixed in accordance with their rules by non-profitmaking organisations with aims of a political, trade-union, religious, patriotic, philosophical, philanthropic or civic nature, provided that this exemption is not likely to cause distortion of competition.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1M
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (m) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1M)
member.remarks: The supply of certain services closely linked to sport or physical education by non-profit-making organisations to persons taking part in sport or physical education.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1N
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (n) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1N)
member.remarks: The supply of certain cultural services, and the supply of goods closely linked thereto, by bodies governed by public law or by other cultural bodies recognised by the Member State concerned.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1O
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (o) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1O)
member.remarks: "The supply of services and goods, by organisations whose activities are exempt pursuant to points (b), (g), (h), (i), (l), (m) and (n), in connection with fund-raising events organised exclusively for their own benefit, provided that exemption is not likely to cause distortion of competition."

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1P
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (p) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1P)
member.remarks: The supply of transport services for sick or injured persons in vehicles specially designed for the purpose, by duly authorised bodies.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_132_1Q
member.summary: Exempt based on article 132, section 1 (q) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-132-1Q)
member.remarks: The activities, other than those of a commercial nature, carried out by public radio and television bodies.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143 of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143)
member.remarks: Exemptions on importation.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1A
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (a) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1A)
member.remarks: The final importation of goods of which the supply by a taxable person would in all circumstances be exempt within their respective territory.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1B
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (b) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1B)
member.remarks: The final importation of goods governed by Council Directives 69/169/EEC (1), 83/181/EEC (2) and 2006/79/EC (3).

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1C
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (c) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1C)
member.remarks: The final importation of goods, in free circulation from a third territory forming part of the Community customs territory, which would be entitled to exemption under point (b) if they had been imported within the meaning of the first paragraph of Article 30

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1D
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (d) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1D)
member.remarks: The importation of goods dispatched or transported from a third territory or a third country into a Member State other than that in which the dispatch or transport of the goods ends, where the supply of such goods by the importer designated or recognised under Article 201 as liable for payment of VAT is exempt under Article 138.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1E
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (e) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1E)
member.remarks: The reimportation, by the person who exported them, of goods in the state in which they were exported, where those goods are exempt from customs duties.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1F
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (f) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1F)
member.remarks: The importation, under diplomatic and consular arrangements, of goods which are exempt from customs duties.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1FA
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (fa) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1FA)
member.remarks: "The importation of goods by the European Community, the European Atomic Energy Community, the European Central Bank or the European Investment Bank, or by the bodies set up by the Communities to which the Protocol of 8 April 1965 on the privileges and immunities of the European Communities applies, within the limits and under the conditions of that Protocol and the agreements for its implementation or the headquarters agreements, in so far as it does not lead to distortion of competition"

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1G
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (g) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1G)
member.remarks: " The importation of goods by international bodies, other than those referred to in point (fa), recognised as such by the public authorities of the host Member State, or by members of such bodies, within the limits and under the conditions laid down by the international conventions establishing the bodies or by headquarters agreements"

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1H
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (h) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1H)
member.remarks: The importation of goods, into Member States party to the North Atlantic Treaty, by the armed forces of other States party to that Treaty for the use of those forces or the civilian staff accompanying them or for supplying their messes or canteens where such forces take part in the common defence effort.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1I
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (i) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1I)
member.remarks: The importation of goods by the armed forces of the United Kingdom stationed in the island of Cyprus pursuant to the Treaty of Establishment concerning the Republic of Cyprus, dated 16 August 1960, which are for the use of those forces or the civilian staff accompanying them or for supplying their messes or canteens.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1J
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (j) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1J)
member.remarks: The importation into ports, by sea fishing undertakings, of their catches, unprocessed or after undergoing preservation for marketing but before being supplied.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1K
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (k) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1K)
member.remarks: The importation of gold by central banks.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_143_1L
member.summary: Exempt based on article 143, section 1 (l) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-143-1L)
member.remarks: The importation of gas through a natural gas system or any network connected to such a system or fed in from a vessel transporting gas into a natural gas system or any upstream pipeline network, of electricity or of heat or cooling energy through heating or cooling networks.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_148
member.summary: Exempt based on article 148 of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-148)
member.remarks: Exemptions related to international transport.

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_148_A
member.summary: Exempt based on article 148, section (a) of Council Directive 2006/112/EC (Code: VATEX-EU-148-A)
member.remarks: Fuel supplies for commercial international transport vessels

member.name: F:PAROCHOSClient.PEPPOLVATExemptionCode.VATEX_EU_148_B
